 playing my necro for 2 years now and posting to the EQ Official Forums and posting here. Nothing has changed. Nothing.</P><P>Dirth's post with quotes from Abashi is spot on. As long as a jackass like Abashi is in charge we are doomed as a class. I feel sorry for everyone that's swalled the whole AA exp scam hook, line and sinker. It's another distraction and time sink that keeps suckers logging in in the hope that they are getting more powerful and trusting in Verant that the AA skills will work. Look at Dire Charm and what a fiasco that skill is. There are only 3-4 zones where a lvl 60 necro could even charm an undead mob for experience. No lich form on a horse?!? Suckers.</P><P>Read what Abashi said, he doesn't want powerful classes--except Warriors, monks, clerics, rogues and chanters. See folks we just ain't in the Vision (TM) anymore. I realize that the following request is about as futile as shouting "stop doing drugs!" in a crack hourse. Please do yourself a favor and get out while you can. </P><P> Dornette<BR> 60 necromancer (retired)<BR> The Nameless</P><P></P><P>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer<BR>The Nameless<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
