        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><BR>  Problem with Absor and Abashi the sock puppets is that they are trained as originally PR/CR people who always have to put a spin on things.  VI doesn't give a rusty F*** what class you play as long as your a paying customer.  There are so few necros now that we no longer have a voice in what gets done, kind of reminds me of small, family owned farms in the midwest.  So few of them, its hard for them to get legislation passed, and only the big corporate farms have a say so they can " bribe " the legislators.  VI is thrilled with people restarting characters cause then you'll pay at least an extra 3-5 months just to get your character where he was before.  Maybe even longer considering a casual player.  As someone has said, there is really no way to revert back to the past.  There are necros here who are good people who give a damn, and know how to play their classes well. Who are in guilds that understand the benefits of a necro to the raid scene, but these people are very lucky, and few and far between ( Members of Triton and Xerexs of FoH come to mind ).  I think that society has become more STFU and deal with it, henceforth people who complain are called whiners.  </P><P><BR>    I think that necros are done pretty much as a class for groups, and are just in the game for the casual gamer who wants to solo.  Its a shame, I remember the days when Druids owned and necros ruled, when rogues were used as primary pullers because they sucked so bad and were expendable and my 49 pet made warriors cry.  But people get tied up in this game so much that they can never leave.  I see EQ becoming basically 5-8 classes, as the others will have become obsolete, and there are no more true newbies to fill the spots.  I haven't seen a true newbie warrior for a very long time.</P><P>   Point of all this is that I think that playing a high lvl necro anymore is akin to banging your head against the wall.  Your better off playing a new class that is wanted.  I wasted 2900 hours of my life playing Lareena.  Considering my wage at this time, that equals to about 87,000 USD.  Maybe I should file a claim against VI for lost wages due to addiction.  Maybe I will :)</P><P><BR>Later, and GL in your new adventuring endevours.</P><P>Lareena D'Inkuth<BR>55 Defiler<BR>Kizek<BR>49 Warrior<BR>Elusion <BR>60 Grave Lord</P><P>Veeshan</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
